The paper deals with distributed beamforming for sensor and relay networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm is bio-inspired and adaptive, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the robustness of the algorithm against the dynamic nature of distributed wireless networks, which is a characteristic of control and systems engineering (cs.SY).
